abstract.text: An instance of this class represents a single SDP service record.

legalNotices.copyright: Copyright © 2025 Apple Inc. All rights reserved.

inlineContent.text: As a service record, an instance of this class has an NSDictionary of service attributes. It also has a link to the IOBluetoothDevice that the service belongs to. The service dictionary is keyed off of the attribute ID of each attribute represented as an NSNumber.

abstract.text: Gain user-space access to Bluetooth devices.
An instance of IOBluetoothDevice represents a single remote Bluetooth device.
Object representing a device inquiry that finds Bluetooth devices in-range of the computer, and (optionally) retrieves name information for them.
An instance of IOBluetoothDevicePair represents a pairing attempt to a remote Bluetooth device.

This class is a representation of a Bluetooth Host Controller Interface that is present on the local computer (either plugged in externally or available internally).
An instance of IOBluetoothL2CAPChannel represents a single open L2CAP channel.
An OBEX Session with a Bluetooth RFCOMM channel as the transport.
An instance of this class represents an RFCOMM channel as defined by the Bluetooth SDP spec..
